  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think even as a first step we don't want users to do their own mapping between the InstantSearch search state and the helper/client one. \r\n\r\nI think what we need is a way to perform the search before any rendering. \r\n\r\nAlso if have a props to set the results state then we need a way to get him back (could be useful for some others use cases). But what I have in mind is more a results state that will be already formatted according to widgets (like the search state). Basically, a way to get back all the provided props of connectors. ",
    "created_at": "2017-02-02T12:40:05Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/1937#issuecomment-276946937",
    "id": 276946937,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1937",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3Njk0NjkzNw==",
