  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I think what we need is a way to perform the search before any rendering.\r\n\r\nThat's the theory for being able to create server side rendering. However with react-instantsearch we have a declarative API based on widget configuration. The whole idea is to keep the configuration definition is a single form. Having a way to configure the search before explicitly writing the widgets means to have another way of defining this configuration, right?",
